Small typos fixed.

Reset kvCacheLength on #clearKVCache (#85)

After `asyncOnReset` I was getting an error when trying to start a new
conversation. After some trial and error I've found that `kvCacheLength`
being reset to `0` fixed the issue. Based on the discussion in
https://github.com/mlc-ai/web-llm/issues/83 I have created this PR to
upstream the fix that worked for me.

fix: Change output to textContent. (#84)

Change output to textContent

Co-authored-by: Jonathan Gao <gsmlg.com@gmail.com>

Update README.md (#66)

Add gem mirror doc for gem/web beginner like me..

Use arrow function to avoid new `this` binding (#58)

While integrating this into a Next.js project I noticed that when it
tried to run `self.updateLastMessage` it would crash Webpack in general
and nothing else would load. Converting this to an arrow function to
maintain the existing `this` binding fixed my issue. I'd reported this
in https://github.com/mlc-ai/web-llm/issues/52.
Update gh-page-config.json with new length config

KV cache creation as a separate func (#53)

This PR changes the creation of KV cache so that it becomes a VM
function that will be invoked before generation.

Enable KV cache reuse across conversations (#51)

Currently, when user enter an input, the behavior is to clear KV cache
and collect all previous conversation history as input prompt to the
model. It becomes extremely slow when the history is large. But clearly,
there exists some redundant kv computation for previous conversations.
We could utilize the kv cache from the last round of conversation to
avoid kv recomputation. This PR enables such optimization.

Change vocab size to support vicuna v1 (#33)

Vicuna v0's vocab_size is 32001, but v1's vocab size is 32000. So we
need to update the manual schedule.

Fix the legalization func of matmul to avoid zero index (#48)

This PR fixes a known issue of the TE legalization func of matmul, which
is used here in the generation of NT matmul. With this PR, there will be
no index 0 whenever the matmul on the particular dimension is not
broadcasting.

Fix RMSNorm workload in MS database (#43)

This PR fixes the hash mismatch issue for the RMSNorm workload, which is
caused by a recent fix in TVM unity.

Minor patch on the annotation and indents of TIR func dispatch (#34)

This PR adds the function annotation to those TIR functions after
scheduling, so that the default GPU schedule pass will skip them. These
annotations are missed to add before.

This PR reindent some of the PrimFunc TVMScript to remove the redundant
indents.

Update README.md (#32)

hugging face -> Hugging Face
Add message when the webgpu is unsupported

Quantization with optional transposition and fusion with matmul (#15)

This PR supports the quantization pass with transposition semantics on
the quantize/dequantize function. With this, we are able to fuse the
dequantize function together with the following GeMV during text
generation, to achieve better performance.

Introducing per-function profiling (#6)

This PR introduces the profiling option to evaluate.py. With this, we
are now able to see the execution time of each function call in the VM.

Use arrow function to avoid new `this` binding (#58)

While integrating this into a Next.js project I noticed that when it
tried to run `self.updateLastMessage` it would crash Webpack in general
and nothing else would load. Converting this to an arrow function to
maintain the existing `this` binding fixed my issue. I'd reported this
in https://github.com/mlc-ai/web-llm/issues/52.

KV cache creation as a separate func (#53)

This PR changes the creation of KV cache so that it becomes a VM
function that will be invoked before generation.
Enable KV cache reuse across conversations (#51)

Currently, when user enter an input, the behavior is to clear KV cache
and collect all previous conversation history as input prompt to the
model. It becomes extremely slow when the history is large. But clearly,
there exists some redundant kv computation for previous conversations.
We could utilize the kv cache from the last round of conversation to
avoid kv recomputation. This PR enables such optimization.
Update index.md
Change vocab size to support vicuna v1 (#33)

Vicuna v0's vocab_size is 32001, but v1's vocab size is 32000. So we
need to update the manual schedule.
Fix the legalization func of matmul to avoid zero index (#48)

This PR fixes a known issue of the TE legalization func of matmul, which
is used here in the generation of NT matmul. With this PR, there will be
no index 0 whenever the matmul on the particular dimension is not
broadcasting.
Fix RMSNorm workload in MS database (#43)

This PR fixes the hash mismatch issue for the RMSNorm workload, which is
caused by a recent fix in TVM unity.
Minor patch on the annotation and indents of TIR func dispatch (#34)

This PR adds the function annotation to those TIR functions after
scheduling, so that the default GPU schedule pass will skip them. These
annotations are missed to add before.

This PR reindent some of the PrimFunc TVMScript to remove the redundant
indents.

Quantization with optional transposition and fusion with matmul (#15)

This PR supports the quantization pass with transposition semantics on
the quantize/dequantize function. With this, we are able to fuse the
dequantize function together with the following GeMV during text
generation, to achieve better performance.
